# 14. Separate Even and Odd Numbers

## Without Built-in Functions

```python
numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]

print("Even:")

for num in numbers:

    if num % 2 == 0:
        print(num)

print("Odd:")

for num in numbers:

    if num % 2 != 0:
        print(num)
```

---

## Using Built-in Functions

```python
numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]

even = [x for x in numbers if x % 2 == 0]
odd = [x for x in numbers if x % 2 != 0]

print(even)
print(odd)
```

